Scholes Street, north side, near the N.W. corner of Bushwick Ave. A view of homes which are soon to be replaced by new low rental Apartment Houses.

July 5, 1935.

P. L. Sperr.

Bushwick Ave., north from Scholes Street, showing the demolished N.W. corner. Upon the site of the old buildings, will be erected the Federal Housing Administration Apartments. From left to right across the clearance, are seen St. John's Evang. Lutheran Church and P.S. No. 117.

August 10, 1936.

P. L. Sperr.
